The paper proposes a new reinforcement learning algorithm that enhances exploration, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm is applied to a simulated environment of unmanned combat aerial vehicle (UCAV) mission execution, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions using replay memory and intrinsic penalty reward, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and reinforcement learning (cs.LG, cs.AI).
